So what hunt, which pack is this?

00:50:04.120 --> 00:50:06.120
This would be the...

00:50:06.120 --> 00:50:08.120
What's it?

00:50:08.120 --> 00:50:10.120
Trudiga.

00:50:10.120 --> 00:50:12.120
Trudiga?

00:50:12.120 --> 00:50:14.120
Trudiga hunt, yes.

00:50:14.120 --> 00:50:16.120
And this is the one you used to follow in your sports car?

00:50:16.120 --> 00:50:18.120
Yes, that's right, yes.

00:50:18.120 --> 00:50:20.120
Oh, and who's this?

00:50:20.120 --> 00:50:22.120
Do you know where this is taken?

00:50:22.120 --> 00:50:24.120
No, I'm not certain of that.

00:50:24.120 --> 00:50:26.120
That's...

00:50:26.120 --> 00:50:28.120
And you see there's two cottages at the side of the six bars.

00:50:28.120 --> 00:50:30.120
Oh, yes, yes.

00:50:30.120 --> 00:50:32.120
And this is...

00:50:32.120 --> 00:50:34.120
What was this? Cairnfip?

00:50:34.120 --> 00:50:36.120
Oh, I don't know, last year?

00:50:36.120 --> 00:50:38.120
Because it looks like it's been closed for years, doesn't it?

00:50:38.120 --> 00:50:40.120
Yes, it does, yes.

00:50:40.120 --> 00:50:42.120
It looks a bit messed up.

00:50:42.120 --> 00:50:44.120
Yes, it's a shame because we've had a lot of fun down there.

00:50:44.120 --> 00:50:46.120
Yeah.

00:50:46.120 --> 00:50:48.120
I was thinking about St Melan's show.

00:50:48.120 --> 00:50:50.120
Yes, that's folded now.

00:50:50.120 --> 00:50:52.120
That's folded.

00:50:52.120 --> 00:50:54.120
But I understand that was a huge event in its time.

00:50:54.120 --> 00:50:56.120
Yes, yes, it was very good.

00:50:56.120 --> 00:50:58.120
We had tremendous times with the show.

00:50:58.120 --> 00:51:00.120
We used to be on the...

00:51:00.120 --> 00:51:02.120
First of all,

00:51:02.120 --> 00:51:04.120
St Melan's show was to be at Remney,

00:51:04.120 --> 00:51:06.120
on the top of

00:51:06.120 --> 00:51:08.120
Remney Hill.

00:51:08.120 --> 00:51:10.120
And then it came then to...

00:51:10.120 --> 00:51:12.120
Oh, what's there now?

00:51:12.120 --> 00:51:14.120
Oh.

00:51:14.120 --> 00:51:16.120
The only one, Cud Curnow.

00:51:16.120 --> 00:51:18.120
Bakers used to

00:51:18.120 --> 00:51:20.120
have the farm.

00:51:20.120 --> 00:51:22.120
Oh.

00:51:22.120 --> 00:51:24.120
Well, all these...

00:51:24.120 --> 00:51:26.120
Oh dear, I can't look at the name.

00:51:28.120 --> 00:51:30.120
Oh, that's silly, isn't it?

00:51:30.120 --> 00:51:32.120
You know, when you go down now towards Newport,

00:51:32.120 --> 00:51:34.120
all these buildings on the right-hand side

00:51:34.120 --> 00:51:36.120
and this left-hand side.

00:51:36.120 --> 00:51:38.120
Like a radiator plant and stuffer.

00:51:38.120 --> 00:51:40.120
That's right, yes. We used to have the show there.

00:51:40.120 --> 00:51:42.120
Did you?

00:51:42.120 --> 00:51:44.120
And then we came then to Kevin Mappley here, down the bottom of this lane,

00:51:44.120 --> 00:51:46.120
where you came over the bridge by the farm park.

00:51:46.120 --> 00:51:48.120
We used to have it there.

00:51:48.120 --> 00:51:50.120
Oh, really? Yes, in the big field there.

00:51:50.120 --> 00:51:52.120
And...

00:51:52.120 --> 00:51:54.120
Oh, yes, and then we went then

00:51:54.120 --> 00:51:56.120
to Jadika House.

00:51:56.120 --> 00:51:58.120
But it was never the same.

00:51:58.120 --> 00:52:00.120
Not really. You know, it was to get...

00:52:00.120 --> 00:52:02.120
I don't know why it was, because it was a nice site.

00:52:02.120 --> 00:52:04.120
But...

00:52:04.120 --> 00:52:06.120
We didn't get the agricultural side of things.

00:52:06.120 --> 00:52:08.120
Yeah, it changed.

00:52:08.120 --> 00:52:10.120
It changed altogether.

00:52:10.120 --> 00:52:12.120
So where it was used to be by Coy Curnow...

00:52:12.120 --> 00:52:14.120
Yes. What was it...

00:52:14.120 --> 00:52:16.120
So where that area is now, it's completely developed, isn't it?

00:52:16.120 --> 00:52:18.120
Oh, yes.

00:52:18.120 --> 00:52:20.120
Was it just farmland then? It was farmland.

00:52:20.120 --> 00:52:22.120
It's hard to imagine.

00:52:22.120 --> 00:52:24.120
It is, isn't it?

00:52:24.120 --> 00:52:26.120
So before the motorway and everything, it was...

00:52:26.120 --> 00:52:28.120
Yes, well, of course they were talking,

00:52:28.120 --> 00:52:30.120
they were putting another road up

00:52:30.120 --> 00:52:32.120
onto the motorway.

00:52:32.120 --> 00:52:34.120
I don't know why that's going to happen, I don't know.

00:52:34.120 --> 00:52:36.120
But it was just farmland?

00:52:36.120 --> 00:52:38.120
Yes, yes, because it was just a little bit there.

00:52:38.120 --> 00:52:40.120
And it was where all the local farmers

00:52:40.120 --> 00:52:42.120
would go along there, would they,

00:52:42.120 --> 00:52:44.120
to present, show their

00:52:44.120 --> 00:52:46.120
livestock? Yes, oh, yes.

00:52:46.120 --> 00:52:48.120
And be a proper agriculture show? Oh, yes, it was.

00:52:48.120 --> 00:52:50.120
Definitely, everything was there.

00:52:50.120 --> 00:52:52.120
And the local show now

00:52:52.120 --> 00:52:54.120
is Macken's Show.

00:52:54.120 --> 00:52:56.120
And that's always on the first Saturday

00:52:56.120 --> 00:52:58.120
of July. And that's a nice little show.

00:52:58.120 --> 00:53:00.120
And that's as big as what St. Melans was.

00:53:00.120 --> 00:53:02.120
But...

00:53:02.120 --> 00:53:04.120
Oh, yes. Oh, yes.

00:53:04.120 --> 00:53:06.120
We've had a lot of fun at the shows.

00:53:06.120 --> 00:53:08.120
Yeah, lovely.

00:53:08.120 --> 00:53:10.120
But things have altered, haven't they, over the years?

00:53:10.120 --> 00:53:12.120
Yeah, they do.

00:53:12.120 --> 00:53:14.120
I was going to ask you about the lighthouse pub.

00:53:14.120 --> 00:53:16.120
Is that something that

00:53:16.120 --> 00:53:18.120
locals would have ever used?

00:53:18.120 --> 00:53:20.120
Was that something people from out of town would use?

00:53:20.120 --> 00:53:22.120
Have you been down to the lighthouse pub?

00:53:22.120 --> 00:53:24.120
Yeah. Oh, it was very pleasant.

00:53:24.120 --> 00:53:26.120
And a lot of people used to walk

00:53:26.120 --> 00:53:28.120
on the bank, you know, across the bank.

00:53:28.120 --> 00:53:30.120
Really? Mm-hmm.

00:53:30.120 --> 00:53:32.120
Would people walk along from the Cardiff

00:53:32.120 --> 00:53:34.120
along here? Yes, well, yes.

00:53:34.120 --> 00:53:36.120
From Remney, perhaps, you know, walk.

00:53:36.120 --> 00:53:38.120
And then you would see them go back and that, you know.

00:53:38.120 --> 00:53:40.120
Oh, yes, yeah.

00:53:40.120 --> 00:53:42.120
It was very pleasant on there. It was a nice day.

00:53:42.120 --> 00:53:44.120
Yeah, it is. It's nice. You know, it's...

00:53:44.120 --> 00:53:46.120
You go up and you can see both sides.

00:53:46.120 --> 00:53:48.120
Yeah. I'm sure it was

00:53:48.120 --> 00:53:50.120
telling me that...

00:53:50.120 --> 00:53:52.120
that people used to

00:53:52.120 --> 00:53:54.120
stay in almost

00:53:54.120 --> 00:53:56.120
like a chalet, seat shack

00:53:56.120 --> 00:53:58.120
in...

00:53:58.120 --> 00:54:00.120
by the sea wall.

00:54:00.120 --> 00:54:02.120
At St. Brides. At St. Brides?

00:54:02.120 --> 00:54:04.120
Yes. Or was it...? They've got caravans

00:54:04.120 --> 00:54:06.120
there now. I don't think he meant

00:54:06.120 --> 00:54:08.120
the caravan that people would rent out

00:54:08.120 --> 00:54:10.120
and would come out for the weekend

00:54:10.120 --> 00:54:12.120
and... Maybe he did mean the caravan, actually.

00:54:12.120 --> 00:54:14.120
I didn't think he did mean that.

00:54:14.120 --> 00:54:16.120
Maybe I got that wrong.

00:54:16.120 --> 00:54:18.120
But you said people would come out for the day

00:54:18.120 --> 00:54:20.120
on their bikes and...

00:54:20.120 --> 00:54:22.120
Oh, a lot of people used to recite

00:54:22.120 --> 00:54:24.120
Lotus in Brides. Really? Yes, yes.

00:54:24.120 --> 00:54:26.120
Yeah. Yes.

00:54:26.120 --> 00:54:28.120
And because they'd had these little tent things,

00:54:28.120 --> 00:54:30.120
wouldn't they? Oh, really?

00:54:30.120 --> 00:54:32.120
Yes, yes. You'd see those, don't they?

00:54:32.120 --> 00:54:34.120
What, like people would camp?

00:54:34.120 --> 00:54:36.120
Yes, yes. They'd sleep in there and then...

00:54:36.120 --> 00:54:38.120
Really? But along by the wall?

00:54:38.120 --> 00:54:40.120
Not so much at all,

00:54:40.120 --> 00:54:42.120
but before they put the

00:54:42.120 --> 00:54:44.120
caravan sites, because there are

00:54:44.120 --> 00:54:46.120
a fair bit of caravan sites at St. Brides

00:54:46.120 --> 00:54:48.120
apparently, which I haven't been there for years.

00:54:48.120 --> 00:54:50.120
Excuse me. And...

00:54:50.120 --> 00:54:52.120
They used to have these

00:54:52.120 --> 00:54:54.120
little tent things, you know, you see

00:54:54.120 --> 00:54:56.120
it on the television, don't they?

00:54:56.120 --> 00:54:58.120
Really? Yes.

00:54:58.120 --> 00:55:00.120
Oh, I didn't know that. Yes, it's...

00:55:00.120 --> 00:55:02.120
Yes, times have changed, haven't they?

00:55:02.120 --> 00:55:04.120
Yeah, they have.

00:55:04.120 --> 00:55:06.120
I said, it's one thing I have to ask you about,

00:55:06.120 --> 00:55:08.120
because I was asking about it, because part of what

00:55:08.120 --> 00:55:10.120
I'm doing is

00:55:10.120 --> 00:55:12.120
talking to people who live

00:55:12.120 --> 00:55:14.120
along the moors, but that

00:55:14.120 --> 00:55:16.120
includes people from the Gypsy community.

00:55:16.120 --> 00:55:18.120
Do you remember

00:55:18.120 --> 00:55:20.120
any Gypsies coming through?

00:55:20.120 --> 00:55:22.120
Well,

00:55:22.120 --> 00:55:24.120
when we had ground,

00:55:24.120 --> 00:55:26.120
we'd entered ground on the corner down

00:55:26.120 --> 00:55:28.120
in St. Brides, and...

00:55:30.120 --> 00:55:32.120
...

00:55:32.120 --> 00:55:34.120
where the Gypsy Caravan Site is now.

00:55:36.120 --> 00:55:38.120
There used to be the old...

00:55:38.120 --> 00:55:40.120
She was an old Gypsy in the proper old...

00:55:40.120 --> 00:55:42.120
....

00:55:42.120 --> 00:55:44.120
Yeah, and they were there for years

00:55:44.120 --> 00:55:46.120
on the corner of our field,

00:55:46.120 --> 00:55:48.120
and we used to have to just pass them,

00:55:48.120 --> 00:55:50.120
you know, to go into the field, and they'd give

00:55:50.120 --> 00:55:52.120
no trouble to us, but these are not Gypsies,

00:55:52.120 --> 00:55:54.120
are they? Not been unkind,

00:55:54.120 --> 00:55:56.120
they'd travel us.

00:55:56.120 --> 00:55:58.120
And, I mean...

00:55:58.120 --> 00:56:00.120
I mean, they've got horses tethered,

00:56:00.120 --> 00:56:05.160
And, well, a friend of mine, she saw this little tiny pony one day and she thought the

00:56:05.160 --> 00:56:07.160
pole was in her way.

00:56:07.160 --> 00:56:08.160
It's sweet.

00:56:08.160 --> 00:56:10.880
She came home and took some hay down to give it on the road.

00:56:10.880 --> 00:56:11.880
You know, it's sad.

00:56:11.880 --> 00:56:13.880
No, these are travellers, more, I think.

00:56:13.880 --> 00:56:19.200
You know, they're not the proper gypsy, I don't think.

00:56:19.200 --> 00:56:20.200
There we are.

00:56:20.200 --> 00:56:21.200
That's life, I suppose, isn't it?

00:56:21.200 --> 00:56:22.200
It is, I suppose.

00:56:22.200 --> 00:56:24.840
And there's so many of them now, isn't there?

00:56:24.840 --> 00:56:29.080
So do you know, you go towards Cardiff and Rumley from where it lives now.

00:56:29.080 --> 00:56:30.080
Yes.

00:56:30.080 --> 00:56:34.600
And, I mean, when you first arrived, was that just agricultural land?

00:56:34.600 --> 00:56:37.080
Oh yes, all just fields.

00:56:37.080 --> 00:56:39.080
It's hard for me to imagine.

00:56:39.080 --> 00:56:40.080
Yes, yes, yes.

00:56:40.080 --> 00:56:47.080
And, of course, there's the KLG, which is a bit firm opposite, isn't there?

00:56:47.080 --> 00:56:48.080
Yeah.

00:56:48.080 --> 00:56:49.080
Doing motor things.

00:56:49.080 --> 00:56:53.480
But, oh yes, it was all, it's most unfortunate.

00:56:53.480 --> 00:56:59.600
I mean, there's a little house there as you go down towards the caravan site, on the right-hand

00:56:59.600 --> 00:57:02.520
side, he was the coalman, Mrs Sadler.

00:57:02.520 --> 00:57:09.120
And I look at it now and I think to myself, oh, if he came back and saw us, yeah, he'd

00:57:09.120 --> 00:57:11.320
be very, very upset about it, you know.

00:57:11.320 --> 00:57:12.320
Yeah.

00:57:12.320 --> 00:57:13.320
He was the coalman.

00:57:13.320 --> 00:57:14.320
Yes.

00:57:14.320 --> 00:57:15.320
So he delivered the coal?

00:57:15.320 --> 00:57:18.320
He delivered the coal, yes, he had the bags of coal.

00:57:18.320 --> 00:57:19.320
Yes.

00:57:19.320 --> 00:57:24.000
Mrs Sadler, his son is still alive and he lives in Rumley.

00:57:24.000 --> 00:57:26.600
I've seen him for some time, actually.

00:57:26.600 --> 00:57:29.600
But as the house was, it was immaculate, you know.

00:57:29.600 --> 00:57:34.600
But as it is now, the slates are gone and it's a mess.

00:57:34.600 --> 00:57:36.600
It breaks his heart.

00:57:36.600 --> 00:57:41.600
Do you remember a nurse, I'm sure it was Nurse Cox, she was the midwife?

00:57:41.600 --> 00:57:43.600
Oh yes, yes, yes.

00:57:43.600 --> 00:57:46.600
Now, she lived on the top of Pendle Land, didn't she?

00:57:46.600 --> 00:57:47.600
That's right.

00:57:47.600 --> 00:57:53.600
Well, there were two cottages there and I'm very friendly with Betty Stevens, her name

00:57:53.600 --> 00:57:55.600
is now, she was Betty Bridge.

00:57:55.600 --> 00:58:02.600
She lived in there, one of those and her brother and those were of course away gone.

00:58:02.600 --> 00:58:04.600
Yes, Nurse Cox.

00:58:04.600 --> 00:58:08.600
And there was another nurse, she lived up there too, because Nurse Cox moved down to

00:58:08.600 --> 00:58:09.600
Castleton.

00:58:09.600 --> 00:58:10.600
Yes.

00:58:10.600 --> 00:58:14.600
On the left-hand side, as you go down off the main road.

00:58:14.600 --> 00:58:17.600
Oh yes, she used to go round delivering the babies.

00:58:17.600 --> 00:58:20.600
Yeah, did she deliver Andrew and your daughter?

00:58:20.600 --> 00:58:22.600
No, I went into Glossop.

00:58:22.600 --> 00:58:23.600
Oh, did you?

00:58:23.600 --> 00:58:25.600
Yes, yes, I went to Glossop test.

00:58:25.600 --> 00:58:26.600
Yeah.

00:58:26.600 --> 00:58:29.600
I just said it with both of them actually.

00:58:29.600 --> 00:58:34.600
But, yes, you bring back memories for me as well.

00:58:34.600 --> 00:58:36.600
Oh, well I met her...

00:58:36.600 --> 00:58:41.600
Well, I suppose we got hedge rows here, where as down there there's the greens.

